I meant generating the size directly to be able to reserve, i.e.
```C++
auto count = fuzzed_data_provider.ConsumeIntegralInRange<size_t>(0, 1000);
std::vector<CAddress> addresses;
addresses.reserve(count);
for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
    addresses.push_back(ConsumeAddress(fuzzed_data_provider));
}
```
like we seem to be doing in [many](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/test/fuzz/bitdeque.cpp#L73) [other](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/test/fuzz/cluster_linearize.cpp#L264-L265) [places](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/test/fuzz/golomb_rice.cpp#L50).

